2. Billing and Procedure Codes (CPT/HCPCS)
The nature of the services performed often indicates a specialist visit.
Evaluation and Management (E&M) Codes: While codes like 99202–99215 are used for office visits, specialist-specific visits may be flagged by different ranges or modifiers.
Specialized Procedures: Procedures unique to a field (e.g., a colonoscopy or a cardiac catheterization) automatically identify the visit as specialized.

Place of Service (POS) Codes: Visits occurring in specialized facilities, such as an Ambulatory Surgical Center (POS 24) or an Inpatient Psychiatric Facility (POS 51), are strong indicators. 
