3. Diagnosis Codes (ICD-10)
Specialist visits are frequently linked to specific, complex ICD-10-CM diagnosis codes that a primary care physician might not typically manage. For example, a diagnosis of a rare genetic disorder or a specific stage of oncology treatment often triggers a referral to a specialist. 
